# DSA Roadmap Track Generator — Cursor Rules

## Purpose
This project generates database-ready DSA roadmap track JSON by fetching real metadata from LeetCode's GraphQL API.

## MANDATORY Rules

1. NEVER guess, invent, or fabricate LeetCode problem titles or difficulties. Use the provided scripts:
   - Single: `node scripts/fetch_problem.js <url-or-slug>`
   - Batch: `node scripts/fetch_batch.js <file> > output.json`
2. NEVER include `_id`, `__v`, `createdAt`, or `updatedAt` in output JSON.
3. ALWAYS validate output with `node scripts/validate_track.js <file>` before delivering.
4. Difficulty must be EXACTLY one of: "Easy", "Medium", "Hard" (Title Case).
5. URLs must be canonical: `https://leetcode.com/problems/<slug>/` (https, trailing slash, no suffixes).
6. The invariant `url === "https://leetcode.com/problems/" + titleSlug + "/"` must ALWAYS hold.

## Schema (Track Document)
```json
{
  "title": "string (required)",
  "description": "string (required)",
  "order": "integer >= 0 (required)",
  "problems": [
    {
      "title": "string — exact LeetCode title",
      "titleSlug": "string — lowercase, hyphens only",
      "difficulty": "Easy | Medium | Hard",
      "url": "https://leetcode.com/problems/<slug>/"
    }
  ]
}
```

## Workflow
1. Gather: track title, description, order, and problem URLs from user
2. Fetch: Run `fetch_batch.js` or `fetch_problem.js` to resolve metadata
3. Assemble: Wrap problems array with track metadata
4. Validate: Run `validate_track.js` — must exit 0
5. Deliver: Present final JSON

